@tarilabs @danielezonca
From a functional point of view DMNRuntimeKB emulates the KieBase. As such, it has to emulate also the functionalities, i.e. returns a PMMLRuntime based on the model name. This is why that parameter is needed - you may see its usage inside DMNRuntimeBuilder.DMNRuntimeKBStatic.
About renaming - I don't see any reason. There is not any other "PMMLRuntime" around; the "legacy" implementation is meant to be removed, and the fact that PMMLRuntime is used for TrustyAI is a detail. From an overall point of view PMML is a sibling of DMN and other models.

